# STAKEHOLDER ANALYSIS: ONLINE LAUNDRY PICKUP & DELIVERY APP

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
This document presents a stakeholder analysis for "FreshFold" – an Online Laundry Pickup & Delivery System.

The platform enables customers to schedule laundry services, select delivery options, make payments, and track order progress. The goal is to improve operational efficiency and enhance customer experience for a local laundry business.

---

## IDENTIFIED STAKEHOLDERS

- Laundry Shop Owner  
- App Developer  
- Finance Personnel  
- Customers  
- Laundry Staff  
- Customer Service Team  
- Pickup/Delivery Personnel  

---

## STAKEHOLDER ANALYSIS MATRIX

| Stakeholder              | Power | Interest | Engagement Strategy |
|--------------------------|--------|----------|----------------------|
| Laundry Shop Owner       | High   | High     | Manage Closely       |
| App Developer            | High   | High     | Manage Closely       |
| Finance Personnel        | High   | Low      | Keep Satisfied       |
| Customers                | Low    | High     | Keep Informed        |
| Laundry Staff            | Low    | High     | Keep Informed        |
| Customer Service Team    | Low    | High     | Keep Informed        |
| Pickup/Delivery Personnel| Low    | Low      | Monitor              |

---

## KEY INSIGHTS

- The Laundry Shop Owner is the primary decision-maker and must be actively engaged throughout the project.  
- The App Developer plays a critical role in system implementation and requires clear, detailed requirements.  
- Customers are highly interested in the service and their feedback is essential for improving user experience.  
- Operational staff (Laundry Staff and Delivery Personnel) are key to execution and should be considered during process design.  

